Now I have the full content. Let me plan both fixes:

### Fix 1: Timer leak on reload (plan-panel.ts)

The problem: On jiti hot reload, the old module's timer closures survive because `stopPlanTimer()` in the new module clears the new module's null references, not the orphaned old intervals.

Fix: Store timer IDs on `globalThis` keyed by a unique symbol, so on reload the new module can find and clear the old intervals.

### Fix 2: `rawText` unbounded growth (activity-feed.ts)

The problem: `state.rawText += text` grows forever. Every call splits ALL accumulated text.

Fix: Cap `rawText` at ~10KB. Trim from the start (preserving the end/latest content) when exceeded.

