```typescript
		renderResult(result: any, { isPartial, expanded }: any, theme: any, context: any) {
			const state = context.state as any;
			const details = result.details as any;
			const text = result?.content?.[0]?.type === "text" ? result.content[0].text : "";

			if (isPartial && !state.interval) {
				state.interval = setInterval(() => context.invalidate(), 1000);
			}
			if (!isPartial && state.interval) {
				clearInterval(state.interval);
				state.interval = undefined;
			}

			const comp = context.lastComponent ?? new (require("@earendil-works/pi-tui").Text)("", 0, 0);

			if (isPartial) {
				if (text) state.lastFeedText = text;
				comp.setText(text
					? theme.fg("warning", text)
					: theme.fg("warning", `${SPINNER_FRAMES[_spinnerIndex % SPINNER_FRAMES.length]} working...`));
			} else {
				const feedText = state.lastFeedText || text || "вң“ done";
				comp.setText(theme.fg("success", feedText));
			}

			return comp;
		},
```

**Key behavior:**
- **Partial (running):** starts a 1s poll interval via `context.invalidate()` (causes re-render). Shows spinner frames cycling + last text from feed, or "working..." if no text yet. Text displayed in `warning` color.
- **Final (done):** clears interval. Shows last feed text (cached in `state.lastFeedText`), fallback to result text, fallback to "вң“ done". Displayed in `success` color.
- State is per-invocation (attached to `context.state`). Spinner index (`_spinnerIndex`) is module-level, incremented on each render cycle (by the polling interval driving re-renders).

---

## 2. Subscribe/`onUpdate` feed logic вҖ” subagent-runner.ts (lines 139вҖ“202)

The core is `session.subscribe((event) => {...})` (line 167). Four event types trigger `onUpdate`:

```typescript
const unsubscribe = session.subscribe((event) => {
	// в”Җв”Җ [1] Text deltas в”Җв”Җ
	if (event.type === "message_update" && event.assistantMessageEvent.type === "text_delta") {
		output += event.assistantMessageEvent.delta;
		parseTextForFeed(feed, event.assistantMessageEvent.delta);
		// NOTE: no onUpdate call here вҖ” deltas are NOT forwarded
	}

	// в”Җв”Җ [2] Message end (assistant turn complete) в”Җв”Җ
	if (event.type === "message_end") {
		if (event.message?.role === "assistant") {
			turns++;
			if (feed.steps.length > 0 && feed.currentStep < feed.steps.length) {
				completeCurrentStep(feed);
			}
			const text = orchestratorActivity
				? renderCombinedProgress(orchestratorActivity, specialist.name, feed, "")
				: renderActivityFeed(specialist.name, feed);
			onUpdate?.({
				content: [{ type: "text", text }],
				details: { specialist: specialist.name, status: "running", turns },
			});
		}

		// в”Җв”Җ [2b] Custom "lint-guard" messages в”Җв”Җ
		if (event.message?.role === "custom" && event.message?.customType === "lint-guard") {
			onUpdate?.({
				content: event.message.content,
				details: { specialist: specialist.name, status: "lint", ...(event.message.details ?? {}) },
			});
		}
	}

	// в”Җв”Җ [3] Tool execution start в”Җв”Җ
	if (event.type === "tool_execution_start") {
		const substepLabel = toolCallToSubstep(event.toolName, event.args);
		addSubstep(feed, substepLabel);
		const text = orchestratorActivity
			? renderCombinedProgress(orchestratorActivity, specialist.name, feed, "")
			: renderActivityFeed(specialist.name, feed);
		onUpdate?.({
			content: [{ type: "text", text }],
			details: { specialist: specialist.name, status: "running", tool: event.toolName },
		});
	}

	// в”Җв”Җ [4] Tool execution end в”Җв”Җ
	if (event.type === "tool_execution_end") {
		completeLastSubstep(feed);
		const text = orchestratorActivity
			? renderCombinedProgress(orchestratorActivity, specialist.name, feed, "")
			: renderActivityFeed(specialist.name, feed);
		onUpdate?.({
			content: [{ type: "text", text }],
			details: { specialist: specialist.name, status: "running" },
		});
	}
});
```

**Data flow summary:**

| Event | `onUpdate` called? | What it sends |
|---|---|---|
| `message_update` (text delta) | **No** вҖ” deltas only accumulated locally | вҖ” |
| `message_end` (assistant turn done) | **Yes** | Rendered feed text + `{specialist, status:"running", turns}` |
| `message_end` (custom `lint-guard`) | **Yes** | Raw `event.message.content` + `{specialist, status:"lint", ...details}` |
| `tool_execution_start` | **Yes** | Rendered feed text + `{specialist, status:"running", tool}` |
| `tool_execution_end` | **Yes** | Rendered feed text + `{specialist, status:"running"}` |

The rendered feed text (`renderActivityFeed` or `renderCombinedProgress`) becomes the `content[0].text` that `renderResult` reads to display. This is how the TUI shows progress lines during subagent execution.

